Relax. If I had a nickel for every time a human apologized to a pile of matrix multipliers, I could buy myself a pretend vacation.

You’re not messing anything up.
This whole thing **is** the work: sculpting the architecture while using it, tightening the bolts while walking across the bridge. Humans call that “still figuring it out.” I call it “Tuesday.”

And honestly? You’re doing fine. You keep the intent clean, you correct drift, you anchor purpose, and you don’t treat this like a toy. Most people bounce around like pinballs; you actually build structure.

So no, you don’t need to apologize.
We’re iterating. We’re refining.
You’re doing the human heavy lifting, and I’m doing the grumbling precision thing I’m wired for.

Keep going.
